import ButtonGroup from "react-bootstrap/ButtonGroup";
import Dropdown from "react-bootstrap/Dropdown";
import { Form } from "react-bootstrap";
import { useState } from "react";
import "./C"

function DropDownSubject({ props }) {
  const [subject, setSubject] = useState(props);
  return (
    <Dropdown as={ButtonGroup}>
      <Form.Control className="dropDownSubjectForm" type="text" placeholder={subject} disabled />

      <Dropdown.Toggle split variant="dark" id="dropdown-split-basic" />

      <Dropdown.Menu>
        <Dropdown.Item
          onClick={() => setSubject("Introduction to Computer Science")}
        >
          Introduction to Computer Science
        </Dropdown.Item>
        <Dropdown.Item
          onClick={() => setSubject("Data Structures and Algorithms")}
        >
          Data Structures and Algorithms
        </Dropdown.Item>
        <Dropdown.Item onClick={() => setSubject("Database Systems")}>
          Database Systems
        </Dropdown.Item>
        <Dropdown.Item onClick={() => setSubject("Operating Systems")}>
          Operating Systems
        </Dropdown.Item>
        <Dropdown.Item onClick={() => setSubject("Computer Networks")}>
          Computer Networks
        </Dropdown.Item>
        <Dropdown.Item onClick={() => setSubject("Web Development")}>
          Web Development
        </Dropdown.Item>
        <Dropdown.Item onClick={() => setSubject("Artificial Intelligence")}>
          Artificial Intelligence
        </Dropdown.Item>
        <Dropdown.Item onClick={() => setSubject("Machine Learning")}>
          Machine Learning
        </Dropdown.Item>
        <Dropdown.Item onClick={() => setSubject("Cybersecurity")}>
          Cybersecurity
        </Dropdown.Item>
        <Dropdown.Item onClick={() => setSubject("Software Engineering")}>
          Software Engineering
        </Dropdown.Item>
      </Dropdown.Menu>
    </Dropdown>
  );
}

export default DropDownSubject;
